bug.short_desc: Evolution reports quota exeeded for Google calendars every morning
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1198509 Screenshot of evolution with "quota exeeded" message
Description of problem: Since last evolution update I get a "quota exeeded" message every morning when starting evolution first time.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): $ rpm -q evolution evolution-3.21.91-2.fc25.x86_64
$ rpm -q evolution-data-server evolution-data-server-3.21.91-1.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: allways
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Make sure you're using Google calendars 2. Open evolution 3.
Actual results: Evolution reports every morning "quota exeeded"
Expected results:
Additional info:

Thanks for a bug report. That's not a "quota exceeded", but "daily limit exceeded", which the server returns when the evolution tries to login to the calendar server. I addressed the real cause of the issue only recently: https://git.gnome.org/browse/evolution-data-server/commit/?id=3fa36f8f0be0107c63aaa254e551e3858c781988
